com.leantegra.wibeat.sdk.monitoring

Class BackgroundScanManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.leantegra.wibeat.sdk.monitoring.ScanServiceManager
      • com.leantegra.wibeat.sdk.monitoring.BackgroundScanManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ServiceConnection

    public class BackgroundScanManager
extends ScanServiceManager
    Allows to scan WiBeat beacons when an application is in the background mode.

    Note: The BackgroundManager typically used in Application class.

    Usage: 
      public class MyApplication extends Application implements BackgroundManagerOld.BackgroundScanListener{
      private BackgroundManagerOld mBackgroundManager;

      @Override
      public void onCreate() {
          super.onCreate();
          //Init background manager
          mBackgroundManager = new BackgroundScanManager(this, this);
          mBackgroundManager.setMonitoringListener(this);
          //Init region list
          ArrayList<Region> regionArrayList = new ArrayList<>(1);
          regionArrayList.add(new Region.Builder(1)
          .addAddress("F2:45:87:51:CD:5F")
          .setProximityZone(ProximityZone.IMMEDIATE).build());
          mBackgroundManager.addMonitoringRegion(regionArrayList);
          //Connect to scan service
          mBackgroundManager.bind();
      }

      @Override
      public void onError(ScanError scanError) {
          //Handle error
      }

      @Override
      public void onEnterRegion(Region region, BaseFrame baseFrame) {
          ...
      }

      @Override
      public void onExitRegion(Region region, BaseFrame baseFrame) {
          ...
      }
  }
